What has that got to do with anything?  Who is the Grand Jury there to
indict?  Idi Amin?  It is a FORMALITY, most Fed Grand Juries are little
more than a rubber stamp.  They want all his stuff - now do you really
think that means 'copies' or do you think that means his equipment is
no longer his for all intents and purposes?   Has government accepted
'copies' provided at the targets discretion in the past?  I will be most
surprised if they don't manage to stick SOMETHING to Grady.  They want
an example to make.  They got one.

